This dish with a few adjustments, is wonderful! First off, if you're not a fan of rich creamy pasta dishes, this is not for you. In contrast, I love creamy dishes. I recommend cutting back on the olive oil as other people have suggested. In the pesto mixture, I added an extra clove of garlic or two. Prior to boiling the heavy cream, I cut slithers of onions and sun dried tomatoes and fried it with a bit of olive oil, and added a dash of white wine (I took this recommendation from a reviewer before me). I also boiled the double cream with added black pepper. This combination was to die for!

Rating: 0
To those who said it was a little bland, try adding a little salt to taste. It sounds dumb, but pesto tends to taste really bland to me (I usually don't add much salt to my foods at all), and invariably add salt. To those who are using 1/2 & 1/2 or non-fat milk- it's alfredo! I understand if we aren't making alfredo in the traditional Italian style, but any Alfredo in the Italian-American tradition is very rich, very fattening, and uses whipping cream- nothing lighter!

